    {
      "name": "AI",
      "description": "Requires **`accessToken`**, **`ideaId`** (run **Ideas → Create idea** first), and server **`OPENAI_API_KEY`**. **`POST /ai/prompt`** streams **NDJSON** (`application/x-ndjson`): optional **`formatted_prompt`**, **`content`** deltas, then **`done`** (usage) or **`error`**. Collection variable **`aiConversationId`** is set on first run (pre-request) and reused for multi-turn tests; clear it in **Variables** to start a new conversation.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send prompt (stream NDJSON)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "let c = pm.collectionVariables.get('aiConversationId');",
                  "if (!c || String(c).trim() === '') {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('aiConversationId', pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is NDJSON', function () {",
                  "  const ct = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
                  "  pm.expect(ct).to.include('application/x-ndjson');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Response has at least one NDJSON line', function () {",
                  "  const lines = pm.response.text().split(/\\r?\\n/).map((l) => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);",
                  "  pm.expect(lines.length, 'lines').to.be.at.least(1);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Stream includes terminal done or error chunk', function () {",
                  "  const lines = pm.response.text().split(/\\r?\\n/).map((l) => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);",
                  "  const chunks = lines.map((l) => JSON.parse(l));",
                  "  const done = chunks.find((c) => c.type === 'done');",
                  "  const err = chunks.find((c) => c.type === 'error');",
                  "  pm.expect(Boolean(done || err), 'done or error').to.be.true;",
                  "  if (done) {",
                  "    pm.expect(done).to.have.property('model');",
                  "    pm.expect(done.usage).to.include.keys('prompt_tokens', 'completion_tokens', 'total_tokens');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/x-ndjson",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tool_type\": \"ai.research\",\n  \"query\": \"Summarize this product idea in two sentences.\",\n  \"context\": {\n    \"idea_id\": \"{{ideaId}}\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"{{aiConversationId}}\"\n  },\n  \"llm_model\": \"gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"temperature\": 0.2,\n  \"max_tokens\": 500,\n  \"idea_id\": \"{{ideaId}}\",\n  \"conversation_id\": \"{{aiConversationId}}\",\n  \"include_formatted_prompt\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ai/prompt",
            "description": "Maps to **`AIViewModel`** / **`AIRemoteDataSource`** — **`postAiPrompt`** streams **`sendPromptStreamForUser`**. **`tool_type`**: **`ai.research`** | **`ai.planning`** | **`ai.mindmap`** | **`ai.highlighted_snippet`**. Set **`include_formatted_prompt`** to **`true`** to receive an initial line with full LLM **`messages`**. **`404`** if the idea cannot be loaded for the user (or conversation cannot be ensured)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Storage",
      "description": "Authenticated **`{{baseUrl}}/storage/...`** routes.\n\n1. **Mint presigned PUT URL** — **`POST /storage/presigned-put`** with **`object_key`** + **`content_type`** (optional **`bucket_name`** if **`CLOUDFLARE_R2_BUCKET_NAME`** is unset). Saves **`storageUploadUrl`**, **`storageObjectKey`**, **`storagePublicUrl`** when returned.\n2. **Upload bytes** — **`PUT`** full URL **`{{storageUploadUrl}}`**. **Do not** send **`Authorization`**. **`Content-Type`** must match mint (**`text/plain`** in examples).\n3. **Record stored file metadata** — **`POST /storage/files`** after R2 has the object. Include **`upload_date`** (**`YYYY-MM-DD`**) and **`upload_time`** (**`HH:mm:ss`**) for the user’s locale (client). Omit **`public_url`** when the API has **`CLOUDFLARE_R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL`** (derived automatically); otherwise add **`\\\"public_url\\\"`** manually or ensure mint returned one into **`storagePublicUrl`**.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Mint presigned PUT URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.upload_url) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('storageUploadUrl', data.upload_url);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (data.object_key) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('storageObjectKey', data.object_key);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (data.public_url) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('storagePublicUrl', data.public_url);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"object_key\": \"postman/{{$guid}}.txt\",\n  \"content_type\": \"text/plain\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/storage/presigned-put",
            "description": "Maps to **`mintPresignedPut`**. **`503`** if R2 env is missing on the server."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload bytes (PUT presigned URL)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "text/plain",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "hello solo"
            },
            "url": "{{storageUploadUrl}}",
            "description": "Upload raw bytes to **`storageUploadUrl`** from **Mint presigned PUT URL**. Run mint first. Body **`hello solo`** is **11** bytes — **`Record stored file metadata`** uses **`file_size`: 11**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Record stored file metadata",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('storedFileId', data.id);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"file_name\": \"postman-test\",\n  \"file_extension\": \"txt\",\n  \"file_size\": 11,\n  \"file_type\": \"document\",\n  \"object_key\": \"{{storageObjectKey}}\",\n  \"content_type\": \"text/plain\",\n  \"upload_date\": \"2026-05-12\",\n  \"upload_time\": \"14:30:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/storage/files",
            "description": "Maps to **`recordStoredFile`** after **`PUT`** succeeds. **`file_type`**: **`document`** | **`presentation`** | **`spreadsheet`** | **`image`** | **`audio`**. If **`400`** mentions **`public_url`**, add **`\\\"public_url\\\": \\\"https://…\\\"`** (or set **`CLOUDFLARE_R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL`** on the API)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
